Belarus: outbreak of serous meningitis in Minsk
-----------------------------------------------
495 cases of enterovirus infection have been registered so far in Minsk
[the capital of Belarus]. According to the Belarus Republic Centre of
Hygiene, Epidemiology and Public Health about 90 of the people affected by
"summer flu" are children. On average about 30 children are being admitted
every day to the children's hospital.
In many cases physicians diagnose serous meningitis, a consequence of
enterovirus infection, which can be transferred through water and food
products. Despite the increased incidence of enteroviral infection, and
serous meningitis in particular, public officials are not considering it an
epidemic . For prevention purposes, chlorination of drinking water has been
undertaken and sanitary and epidemiologic control in food producing
factories is being increased.
--
Nilufar Rakhmanova MD
Master of Public Health
Boston University
School of Public Health
<rakhmanovan@yahoo.com>
